<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06185021 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06185021 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  OPINION; LETTER  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Who is making demands on the Syrian and Iraqi Arabs to grant the Kurds anindependent state in their ancient homeland on the &quot;West Bank&quot; of the TigrisRiver?;    For years the Iraqis have been Arabizing Kurdistan, bringing inArabs from other parts of the Arab world, including Egyptians, Palestinians,Yemenis and Bedouins, to live in lands depopulated of its indigenous Kurdishinhabitants.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Editorial  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  SILENCE ON THE BETRAYAL OF KURDS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Letters to the Editor  </MEMO><TEXT>     Now the depopulation of Iraqi Kurdistan has been greatly accelerated asKurdish refugees have fled for their lives to Turkey and Iran.;    Why has theUnited Nations been so silent on the plight of the Kurds over the years?Perhaps it has something to do with every time the Kurdish question isdebated, the Arab states, in concert with the Turks, Iranians and the Soviets,have effectively blocked debate and refocused it on Israel.;    -- NaomiParker; San Jose;  PLEDGE ALLEGIANCE TO MASS TRANSIT; The proposed price hikefor bus and light rail fares will discourage those who already use masstransit and those who might experiment with it. But if the countyTransportation Agency won't tighten its belt, I will.;    Using publictransportation is a stance, a statement as well as an economical practicality.I will not surrender to compliance with national and environmental suicide. Iwill not be a slave to oil and insurance. Besides, I'm a student and couldn'tafford to anyway.;    I'll pay more to ride the bus and still save if youconsider the costs of driving, the initial cost of a car, auto insurance,maintenance, fuel and tickets. I'll sleep better at night. I'll be able to paymy rent and have a clear conscience because I'm not contributing to pollutantsor partaking of the quicksand oil establishment.;    Please write the SantaClara County Transportation Agency to oppose the price hike.;    -- DanielOchieng Forde; San Jose;  Face up to; Democrats' failure; I wonder if Carl M.Cannon is just envious of the White House or sorry the national Democrats havewon only three of the last 10 presidential elections (Perspective, June 23)?;   How else do you explain his complaint -- yes, folks, there's just too muchrampant enthusiasm, too much irrepressible optimism for this country's owngood.;    Yes, the Democrats are a bunch of &quot;sticks in the mud.&quot; That's beenwell known for a long time. Yes, the major national media are loyal servantsof the Democratic Party. That's well known, too, and explains the currentblood-lust for Gov. John Sunnunu's head.;    Cannon thinks President Bush issome mindless &quot;cheerleader&quot; crippled with &quot;classic denial.&quot;;    But tocomplain that voters are neurotic as a result of Republican campaignstrategies is merely for Cannon to project his own confusions and inadequacieson about everyone else. Face it, the voters are not messed up. The Democratsare.;    -- Mark J. Johnson; Redwood City;  Prop. 13 formula; doesn't add up;R.G. Winslow, Jr. is the one who should &quot;get real&quot; about Proposition 13(Letters, June 22).;    Using his own figures, he pays $5,300 in propertytaxes and interest. From this he gets a tax break of $1,910 leaving anout-of-pocket expense of $3,390.;    The new owner spends a gross amount of$28,000 for which he gets a tax break of $10,450. Thus his out-of-pocketexpense amounts to $17,550 for the same property. Where is the justice inthis?;    -- Jean M. F. Dubois; Los Gatos  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910703  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  565  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday July 3, 199